messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /api/orders

All HTTP methods acceptable (overrides others)?
- false

Acceptable methods for /api/orders (based on code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- server.js mounts the router at the prefix "/api/orders" via app.use('/api/orders', orderRoutes).
- In routes/orderRoutes.js the route for '/' (i.e. the router root) is defined as:
  - router.route('/').post(protect, addOrderItems).get(protect, admin, getOrders)
  This explicitly registers POST and GET handlers for the full path /api/orders.
- There are no explicit .head(), .options(), .trace(), .put(), .delete(), or .patch() handlers registered for '/' in the code, so those methods are not considered acceptable per the instruction to base acceptance on the code (not runtime/Express behavior).
- Note: the code does register additional order-related endpoints (for completeness):
  - GET /api/orders/mine -> getMyOrders
  - GET /api/orders/{id} -> getOrderById
  - PUT /api/orders/{id}/pay -> updateOrderToPaid
  - PUT /api/orders/{id}/deliver -> updateOrderToDelivered
  These do not change the method availability for the /api/orders path itself.
